@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix xml: <http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix dc: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .

<http://data.europa.eu/eli/dir/2018/2001/oj>
  dc:title "EU_32018L2001_Title_0_Chapter_0_Section_0_Article_16" ;
  dc:description "Organisation and duration of the permit-granting process"@en .

<http://data.europa.eu/eli/dir/2018/2001/oj>
  skos:notation "32018L2001" ;
  dc:identifier "EU_32018L2001_Title_0_Chapter_0_Section_0_Article_16" .

_:b1 
  a <http://www.aksw.org/KC> ;
  rdfs:label "Member States shall set up or designate one or more contact points"@en ;
  dc:description "The contact points shall, upon request by the applicant, guide through and facilitate the entire administrative permit application and granting process."@en .

_:b2 
  a <http://www.aksw.org/KC> ;
  rdfs:label "The contact point shall guide the applicant through the administrative permit application process in a transparent manner"@en ;
  dc:description "up to the delivery of one or several decisions by the responsible authorities at the end of the process, provide the applicant with all necessary information and involve, where appropriate, other administrative authorities."@en .

_:b3 
  a <http://www.aksw.org/KC> ;
  rdfs:label "The contact point shall make available a manual of procedures for developers of renewable energy production projects"@en ;
  dc:description "and shall provide that information also online, addressing distinctly also small-scale projects and renewables self-consumers projects."@en .

_:b4 
  a <http://www.aksw.org/KC> ;
  rdfs:label "Without prejudice to paragraph 7, the permit-granting process referred to in paragraph 1 shall not exceed two years for power plants"@en ;
  dc:description "including all relevant procedures of competent authorities. Where duly justified on the grounds of extraordinary circumstances, that two-year period may be extended by up to one year."@en .

_:b5 
  a <http://www.aksw.org/KC> ;
  rdfs:label "Without prejudice to paragraph 7, the permit-granting process shall not exceed one year for installations with an electrical capacity of less than 150 kW"@en ;
  dc:description "Where duly justified on the grounds of extraordinary circumstances, that one-year period may be extended by up to one year."@en .

_:b6 
  a <http://www.aksw.org/KC> ;
  rdfs:label "Member States shall facilitate the repowering of existing renewable energy plants"@en ;
  dc:description "by ensuring a simplified and swift permit-granting process. The length of that process shall not exceed one year."@en .

_:b7 
  a <http://www.aksw.org/KC> ;
  rdfs:label "Member States may establish a simple-notification procedure for grid connections for repowering projects"@en ;
  dc:description "as referred to in Article 17(1). Where Member States do so, repowering shall be permitted following notification to the relevant authority where no significant negative environmental or social impact is expected."@en .

_:b8 
  a <http://www.aksw.org/KC> ;
  rdfs:label "The deadlines established in this Article shall apply without prejudice to obligations under applicable Union environmental law"@en ;
  dc:description "to judicial appeals, remedies and other proceedings before a court or tribunal, and to alternative dispute resolution mechanisms, including complaints procedures, non-judicial appeals and remedies, and may be extended for the duration of such procedures."@en .

